Preheat your oven to 200°C and bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{pinch}. Chop the @halloumi{125g} into 2cm chunks. Trim the @courgette{1},
halve lengthways then chop widthways into 2cm chunks. Halve and peel the
@red onion{1}. Chop each half into quarters. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard
the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Pop the halloumi and chopped veggies on a #large lined baking tray{} and drizzle
with @oil{}. Sprinkle on the @dried oregano{1%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and
season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out in
one layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.
Turn halfway through cooking.

Add the @penne pasta{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook for
~{10%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{} then return to the pan (off the heat) and
drizzle with @oil{} to stop it sticking. Roughly chop the @sundried tomatoes{15g}.

When the veggies and halloumi are done, transfer them to an #ovenproof dish{}
along with the cooked wheat pasta, sundried tomatoes and @finely chopped tomatoes
with onion and garlic{1/2%100g}. Add in half the @fresh basil{} then stir
everything together.

Sprinkle the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20g} over the top then bake on the
top shelf of your oven until golden and bubbly, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Divide the halloumi wheat pasta bake between your plates and serve. Enjoy!